SIMPLE: forcible
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Forcible
<hw>For"ci*ble</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <ety>[Cf. OF.
<ets>forcible</ets> forcible, <ets>forceable</ets> that may be
forced.]</ety> <sn>1.</sn> <def>Possessing force; characterized by
force, efficiency, or energy; powerful; efficacious; impressive;
influential.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>How <qex>forcible</qex> are right words!</q> <rj><qau>Job. vi.
2<?/.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Sweet smells are most <qex>forcible</qex> in dry substances, when
broken.</q> <rj><qau>Bacon.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>But I have reasons strong and <qex>forcible</qex>.</q>
<rj><qau>Shak.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>That punishment which hath been sometimes <qex>forcible</qex> to
bridle sin.</q> <rj><qau>Hooker.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>He is at once elegant and sublime, <qex>forcible</qex> and
ornamented.</q> <rj><qau>Lowth (Transl. )</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>Violent; impetuous.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Like mingled streams, more <qex>forcible</qex> when joined.</q>
<rj><qau>Prior.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>3.</sn> <def>Using force against opposition or resistance;
obtained by compulsion; effected by force; <as>as, <ex>forcible</ex>
entry or abduction</as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>In embraces of King James . . . <qex>forcible</qex> and
unjust.</q> <rj><qau>Swift.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><cs><col><b>Forcible entry and detainer</b></col> <fld>(Law)</fld>,
<cd>the entering upon and taking and withholding of land and tenements
by actual force and violence, and with a strong hand, to the hindrance
of the person having the right to enter.</cd></cs></p>

<p><syn><b>Syn.</b> -- Violent; powerful; strong; energetic; mighty;
potent; weighty; impressive; cogent; influential.</syn>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Forcible-feeble</ent>⟦br⟧
